org.osate.xtext.aadl2.agcl.analysis.misc

Class Settings

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.osate.xtext.aadl2.agcl.analysis.misc.Settings
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    DefaultSettings
    Deprecated.

    @Deprecated
public class Settings
extends java.lang.Object
    Objects of this class store general settings for the AGCL plug-in. These are:
    • projectDir: the project directory ("project.dir" in settings.conf)
    • templatesDir: the templates directory ("templates.dir" in settings.conf)
    • nusmvSessionTemplate: the NuSMV session script template ("templates.nusmv.session_script" in settings.conf)

    The reason to have a Settings class and not just a Properties class is that this class provides its clients with normalized, absolute paths according to the runtime platform, whereas the Properties class simply stores plain String values for these paths, which may not be platform-independent.

    Author:
    Ernesto Posse
